What is React js
-------------------
1. react js is an open-source js library developed and maintained by facebook
2. it's widely used for building user interfaces, especially for single page applications and complex web interfaces.
3. it breaks down a whole website into small, manageable pieces called components
4. it enables developers to create dynamic, responsive, and reusable UI compnents, enchancing the efficiency of the development process



why React js
--------------
1. speed :- react uses of the virtual DOm aloows for efficient updates and rendering, resulting in faster and more responsive user interfaces
2. reusability :- React allows components based approach where the component can be reusable this leads to cleaner code, easier maintenance, and better collaboration among team members
3. job market :- it has high demand! companies like netflix, AirBnd, instagram etc.
4. Rich Ecosystem And Tooling :- react is supported by a vast ecosysytem of libraries, tools and frameworks that enhance its capabilities and help developers build robust applications more efficiently


